                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Meyer</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1903-01-10">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 10, 1903</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Hay states that Mr. Bowen will leave Caracas for Washington on January 11;
                    that he is anxious for the raising of the blockade at the earliest moment
                    possible, on account of the fact that the scarcity of provisions in Venezuela
                    threatens general distress. Mr. Hay has answered Mr. Bowen that no preliminaries
                    can be adjusted before his arrival, and that the raising of the blockade may
                    depend upon the sufficiency of Venezuela’s guarantee. Mr. Meyer is directed to
                    suggest to the Italian minister for foreign affairs that the matter might be
                    taken into consideration with a view to early determination.)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
